==Latin==
===Etymology===
Either derived from (of cognate with) Greek [[ἐβδομάς]] (''hebdomás'')

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/ˈhɛːb.dɔ.mas/}}
===Noun===
'''hebdomas''' (''genitive'' '''[[hebdomadis]]'''); {{f}}, ''[[Wiktionary Appendix:Latin third declension|third declension]]''

# [[seven]]
# [[week]]; seven days

===Usage notes===
*The usual word for "seven" as an adjective in Latin is [[septem]].
*The word [[septimana|septimāna]] replaced hebdomas as the word for "week" in later Latin.

